entry.title: Fix hover card footer icon from popping in
entry.content:
The tab hover card footer icon was seen popping in when users have a lot

of tabs open due to the icon being painted on another layer. Since the

icon is being painted on another layer, the hover card bubble doesn't

clip the icon when the icon is painted before the footer fully expands.



This CL fixes this bug by having the hover card footer clip the primary

icon view. We paint only the icon that is fading out to another layer

and keep the primary icon view on the same layer as the footer (similar

to how the thumbnail view crossfades the hover card thumbnail image).



Video of footer with fix: https://screencast.googleplex.com/cast/NTY5MjgzMTQ0MTA5MjYwOHxiMGQ4ZGQ3Zi02MQ

entry.title: [ProfilesReordering] Add a recovery logic for the profile order pref
entry.content:
A recovery will happen if in the pref list:

- a profile key is missing.

- a profile key is duplicated.

The recovery will reinitialise the pref to the alphabetically ordered

list of profiles per profile local name.

This initialisation will also trigger the first time the pref is created.

entry.title: Let provisional frames use a provisional probe sink
entry.content:
For cross-process frame swap, the DevTools agent

host is not connected to a provisional frame until

commit.

However, for local frame swaps, we're currently

not preventing a provisional frame from emitting

events via the DevTools agents associated to its

local root, which may create confusion for the client,

as both the old frame and a new provisional LocalFrame

have the same DevTools frame token.



This CL brings the behavior of a local frame swap

closer to the cross-process case by assigning a new

dummy probe sink to a provisional subframe until it's

committed, and swapping the sink with the old frame

when frame swap occurs.



Bug: 936696, 1455307



See discussion at https://crrev.com/c//4686136 for

additional context.

entry.title: [uia] Always create ITextProvider::GetVisibleRanges on leaf nodes
entry.content:
This CL aims to address a bug where if `GetVisibleRanges` was called on

the complex content editable structures such as the following:



one two


three four


five six




it would first return one range with the text of the three and

return two more empty ranges. Then, if `FindText` was called on this

range, it would not find text beyond the first three characters.



This was in part caused since the range was created on the first

element which then would cause `FindText` to interpret it's text

as three embedded object characters (due to the three child divs)

and so the text would not be found.



The fix consists on simply making sure that the range created by

`GetVisibleRanges` were created on the leaf text nodes.

entry.title: [iOS] Fix sign-in in progress in SigninPromoMediator
entry.content:
This patch resolve a DCHECK signs in with syncpassphrase and then

turns on sync in bookmark.



The issue was sync service notifications was received before the

sign-in was done. Those notifications were setting

`self.signinInProgress` to NO.



To fix the issue, `signinInProgress` becomes private and is only set

when sign-in starts and stops.

Also private `initialSyncInProgress` property is introduced to track

the initial sync. It is set to YES (if needed) when sign-in is done.



For the public `signinInProgress` is replaced by

`showSigninOrInitialSyncSpinner`. This value is YES if either

`signinInProgress` or `initialSyncInProgress` is YES.

entry.title: Fix dangling pointer in HttpsOnlyMode[Allow|Enforce]list
entry.content:
StatefulSSLHostStateDelegate owns a HttpsOnlyModeAllowlist and a

HttpsOnlyModeEnforcelist object, passing them a pointer to the Clock

that it owns. However, when setting a Clock object in testing via

StatefulSSLHostStateDelegate::SetClockForTesting(), the pointers held

by the HttpsOnlyModeAllowlist and HttpsOnlyModeEnforcelist would very

briefly be dangling between the Delegate taking ownership of the new

Clock object (causing the old Clock object to be destroyed) and a new

raw pointer to the new Clock object being passed into the Allowlist

and Enforcelist objects. This fixes that brief dangling (which caused

the DanglingPtr detector to trigger) by resetting the Clock pointer in

the Allowlist/Enforcelist to nullptr before setting the new Clock

object.

entry.title: Update form managers from server predictions.
entry.content:
Dynamic changes to a password form can cause its content and form

signature to change. However, PWM does currently not handle the

following flow of events correctly:



1) Form gets recognized (and potentially filled) by PWM, say because

it is a login form.

2) The page then destroys the password element. This changes the form's

signature and new server predictions are requested.

3) The server predictions for the resulting form (same renderer id, but

different signature) arrive from Autofill.

4) PasswordManager::ProcessAutofillPredictions() finds that there is

already a PasswordFormManager (because look-up happens via renderer

id) and therefore performs no update.



The correct behaviour in 4) would be to update the password form

manager if the observed form has changed and trigger filling.



This CL makes that change. It uses the same call paths (and thus

criteria) as dynamic form updates reported by the renderer side and

processed inside of CreateFormManagers.
